# ========================================
# 🔐 SECURITY - SENSITIVE FILES
# ========================================
# CRITICAL: Never commit files containing credentials, tokens, or secrets
# These patterns prevent accidental exposure of sensitive information

# Credentials and tokens (actual files with secrets)
CREDENTIALS_ET_TOKEN.md
CREDENTIALS_*.md
!CREDENTIALS_*.template.md
TOKEN_REAL*.md
TOKENS_*.md
SECRET_*.md
!SECRET_*.template.md

# API keys and certificates
*.key
!public.key
*.keystore
*.p12
*.pfx

# Local credentials files
*.local.md
*_LOCAL.md

# Allowed: Setup guides and documentation (no actual secrets)
# GITHUB_TOKEN_SETUP.md - Instructions only
# scripts/setup-git-credentials.sh - Script with placeholders
# backend/src/**/*token*.ts - Code files (DTOs, services)
nul

# ==========================================================================
# MCP servers (v1.4.x — persistent memory + codebase knowledge graph)
# ==========================================================================
# Local persistent memory graph written by @modelcontextprotocol/server-memory.
# Contains developer-specific session-to-session facts.
.claude/memory.jsonl
.claude/memory.jsonl.backup*

# SQLite index + embeddings cache for @sdsrs/code-graph (AST + FTS5).
# Regenerated on demand via `npx @sdsrs/code-graph rebuild-index --confirm`.
.code-graph/

# Claude Code worktrees — ephemeral per-session checkouts of the repo at
# .claude/worktrees/<slug>/. Should NEVER be committed to the parent repo
# (each worktree has its own .git pointer + branch). Added Track D.2 (2026-05-14).
.claude/worktrees/
